article.headline: N. Iowa 61, Denver 56
article.story: CEDAR FALLS, Iowa -- Center Jordan Eglseder scored 17 points to lead Northern Iowa past Denver 61-56 on Saturday in the season opener for both teams. Freshman point guard Johnny Moran had 14 points and grabbed 10 rebounds -- including a 3 with 41 seconds left to push the Panthers lead to 57-51 -- and Ali Farokhmanesh scored 13 for Northern Iowa (1-0). Nate Rohnert had a game-high 20 points and five rebounds for Denver (0-1), which led 20-19 at halftime. Kyle Lewis scored 15 points and Rob Lewis added 13. Eglseder shot 8-of-9 from the floor as Northern Iowa picked up its sixth straight season-opening win.
